\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Just your father would have his in the evening?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Meal when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 How about jams or bottled fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. Yes, she did do a little of that but not too much. No, not too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, she didn't - we didn't like them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 How about homemade wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Or homemade medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Was any beer brewed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 This had more or less died out by that time had it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did your father or mother grow any of their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No. No garden much, no there was no back - no, very small yard, very small it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did they buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Well there wasn't - dried they might have but t
here's not much tinned in those days, no. Not much. They didn't - they didn't care for it, the tinned food, they didn't care for it. They'd sooner have it fresh you know. Well we had fresh fruit from my aunts in Buckinghamshire you see, they used to send 
up fruit, yes. They had great gardens there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 So you didn't keep any livestock if you didn't have much garden, any hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Tinned meat? I don't remember. No, they didn't trust the tinned meat. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbits from poachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Oh yes, they have rabbits and perhaps p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13372087\charrsid3473785 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 ultry. But mostly when the aunts sent it you see. Yes, when it came from Buckinghamshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Talk at mealtimes? No, we didn't like that. Mother didn't like that, no, she didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did you ever notice your mother having a small portion so that the others could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, I don't remember, we always seemed to have equal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 You always had equal shares?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, it was - gave us that meal you see and if you didn't want }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13372087\charrsid3473785 it }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 then leave it. If we wanted more it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 So you could always ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 You could always - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 What was your parents attitude if you left any food uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Well we - she thought perhaps you weren't well you see. That's all. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Some people make children eat their meal up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
Yes, that's right. I don't remember - much illness. No. I - I don't think I was ever ill. My father was never ill, nor am I. Never ill. Until he died. He had - now I can't think - something to do with 
the blood. I daresay you'd know it if I could think of it. Just can't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 A type of an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13372087\charrsid3473785 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
emia?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
Yes, it - I don't know what they call it now, I've heard it such a lot, such a lot of people have had it, I was trying last night to think of it but
 I can't. It was the heart 'cos hen I went up to see him last time he said, have you seen anything like this? He pulled his shirt open and it was all blue. So I said, oh no. He said, it looks like I've b-en knocked down by a lorry. I said, yes it does. It
 was very painful but he didn't live very long. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 But he'd been in good health up 'til then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
Up 'til then he'd never had an illness, and mother the same but when dad died she just went to pieces. She didn't live - yes - she didn't live a year after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Were you taught to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did you have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Oh yes, yes. We had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Could you bring books or toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Oh no. No, not to the meal table, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Well you could ask for it. Yes. It wasn't so very stiff but severe in some ways. Yes. Yes she was. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did Ada eat with you when she was there during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes, she didn't stop for meals. No. She had a sister went out to business too so she got the meal for that sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 So she was never there mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, she wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Was she - oh yes. Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, yes, yes, you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did she show affection much, was she demonstrative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 I don't - remember. No. She was very kind, she was very
 kind - there was a - person lived next to us and she had a little girl, pretty little girl, I was thinking about that little girl quite recently you know, just like a little angel and I said to mother, isn't that little girl like an angel. She said, yes 
s
he is. And she died. And I've never forgotten it, but - then I said to my mother when she had another girl, she said, I don't want her to die and mother said, don't worry, do what I did. And she did. She used to go in to her. And she grew - she's a fine g
irl. And she said, that's thanks to Mrs Curry. Of course it wasn't but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Your mother showed concern for people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 On the whole an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes, she was, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Oh
 yes, he was very nice too. Yes, yes he was, he would help anyone. I've heard him - I came home day and I met a man I'd seen with my father, so he said, aren't you miss Curry? I said, yes. He said, oh - your father was so kind to me, I'll never forget him
.
 He said - he - he was a tailor, my father was, of course they had slack times and he said - this man - he was a tailor but he wasn't very good. So - and he had a family and was rather poor so father - my father said, well don't worry, I'll come and see y
ou. So he went to see him and he said he was poor. He was poor and he'd only got half a crown himself. So he gave that to the wife and he said - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13372087\charrsid3473785 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 han't be very long, he'll be back soon and he took him right to a - a - to a tailors shop which he knew, a little way out - what did you call it - not anything particular. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 A working class tailor or something like this you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. He said, I know you Mr Curry don't I? He said, yes, I think you do. So he said, did you want to work? He said, yes,
 I've come after a job, he said, I want this one with me. Oh, he said, I couldn't take him. He said, well if you can't take him you can't take me. So he says, oh - I'll - I'll give him a little job but he's not much of a tailor. So}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13372087\charrsid3473785  he said, no, but - he - he wan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
ts a living the same as us all. So he did, he went there to work and - my father didn't stop long, he came away. And that was the man who called and said - oh yes. He said, he never looked back. But he always was very kind - they both were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 How did your parents expect you children to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 
Oh well, we were always taught to respect them. I don't think there was a mother or father like them. When the girls would say at school my mother did this - oh - my mother wouldn't - my mother wouldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Even as a child you were quite conscious that your parents were good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. Yes. Yes, they were very god.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 They didn't emphasise anything in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No. We got along pretty well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 No, I don't think so, I don't remember - it being necessary to hit back. No. I used to come al
ong to - from school alone. The other girls used to come along of course together, friends, but - I seemed to be alone, you know what I mean. And - when the boys - sometimes when the boys came blustering home from school fighting and running after the gir
ls my - one run - ran up to me one days and I'd got long hair, the other boys said, don't touch her, she's Tommy Curry's sister. So I was always allowed to come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 You had your brothers to do your fighting for you?
