rning at school now? And I said to him one day, we are learning Macbeth. He said, Macbeth? I said, yes. Well, he said, I never knew a girls school learned Macbeth. So he said, well tell me what you've said - what part you learn. Of course I - oh he said, 
that's not the way to say it. Well of course I - I had to follow at school because - and of course he put emphasis on where it should be you know and I couldn't find that out for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 So he'd be quite helpful with your reading?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. Yes,
 yes. Oh yes, he used to help me a lot with school you see and - I know I have said - when we had a - inspectors come to school, ask you questions and nobody could answer, but I could. Yes. So when they went they said, come here Julia Curry, where did you
 hear that? I said, well my father told me. What is he? I said, tailor. They couldn't make it out. Then you see he'd had the education. But ours was just a church school, a very nice school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 I suppose it was quite unusual to have a university man tailoring in those days?
