ording. The - the little girl was very forward, she would sit up pretty quick. But the next one, the boy, he wasn't forward at all. You would put him in a chair you know and - he was a big child too and he never seemed - he didn't seem to have - con}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224381\charrsid3473785 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 rol of
 the limbs you know like the others did. And he'd walk along like that you know. But he was quite all right, I asked the doctor, oh he'll be quite all right. He was too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 So you'd put them up to the table as soon as they were table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15862227 JG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 Yes. Yes, yes, that's right. They'd be perhaps three - two - three years old. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009757 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid138725\charrsid3473785 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
