In Faraday house and - well - he started at a place that they offered him at school, he didn't like that. So he left that and he went to - to - what was the big school, no
t the Town Hall, the -s oh dear - where they go sometimes for - Polytechnic, forgot it, the Polytechnic. He went to the Polytechnic see and took some - lessons there and from there he went to - he went to - leatherwork, to do leatherwork. Well he got on v
e
ry well with that but of course he had to join up from there, joined up. And then he - when he came back again - I said, what about the leatherwork now? Don't want to go to it. So what are you going to do? Oh don't worry mum, I'll find something. So he di
